  "id": "2b51a328fc4eb47b",
  "fields": {
    "apply_url": "https://jobs.ashbyhq.com/snowflake/35ca0435-7155-4797-8a45-f978f8bc2cff/application",
    "company": "Snowflake",
    "compensation": "",
    "content_hash": "2b51a328fc4eb47b",
    "department": "Marketing",
    "description": "At Snowflake, we are powering the era of the agentic enterprise. To usher in this new era, we seek AI-native thinkers across every function who are energized by the opportunity to reinvent how they work. You don’t just use tools; you possess an innate curiosity, treating AI as a high-trust collaborator that is core to how you solve problems and accelerate your impact. We look for low-ego individuals who thrive in dynamic and fast-moving environments and move with an experimental mindset — who rapidly test emerging capabilities to discover simpler, more powerful ways to deliver results. At Snowflake, your role isn't just to execute a function, but to help redefine the future of how work gets done.\n\n\nABOUT THE ROLE\n\nSnowflake is seeking an experienced, strategic Senior Manager of Executive Communications to help shape and scale communications for our corporate leadership, including the CEO, CFO, Chief People Officer, and VP of Strategic Initiatives.\n\nThis role sits at the center of Snowflake’s leadership narrative, translating business strategy into clear, compelling communications that resonate with employees, customers, partners, and the broader market. You will serve as a trusted advisor and operator, driving executive messaging across internal and external platforms while ensuring alignment, consistency, and impact.\n\nThis role is for a communications leader who thrives at the intersection of strategy, storytelling, and execution and who is comfortable influencing at the highest levels of the organization.\n\n\nKEY RESPONSIBILITIES\n\nExecutive Communications Leadership\n\n - Serve as a core communications partner for Snowflake’s corporate leadership, supporting a broad range of internal and external communications initiatives\n\n - Shape executive messaging and positioning, and tone to ensure clarity, credibility, and alignment with company strategy\n\nExecutive Messaging \u0026 Thought Leadership\n\n - Lead development of executive messaging, talking points, and written communications across key moments including company milestones, financial announcements, cultural initiatives, and strategic priorities\n\n - Shape and produce executive thought leadership content, including social media posts, op-eds, and long-form narratives, in close partnership with PR, social, and marketing teams\n   \n\nBriefings \u0026 Strategic Materials\n\n - Own creation of executive briefing materials for speaking engagements, employee forums, and key communications engagements\n   \n\n - Synthesize complex business and technology topics into concise, executive-ready messaging\n   \n\nCommunications Planning \u0026 Governance\n\n - Build and manage a centralized view of executive communications activity, including speaking engagements, announcements, and leadership moments\n\n - Maintain and evolve a centralized executive messaging library to ensure consistency and reuse across teams\n   \n\nCross-Functional Alignment\n\n - Partner closely with Marketing, PR, Investor Relations, People, and Product Communications to align executive messaging across audiences and channels\n\n - Ensure executive communications reinforce Snowflake’s broader narrative, values, and strategic priorities\n   \n\nInternal Communications \u0026 Employee Engagement\n\n - Support leadership communications for company-wide moments such as All Hands and employee announcements\n\n - Partner with People Communications to support leadership messaging related to culture, talent, and organizational change\n\nResearch \u0026 Strategic Opportunity Identification\n\n - Evaluate and prioritize external forums, events, and awards that advance Snowflake’s executive visibility and thought leadership goals\n\n - Provide strategic recommendations on where and how senior leaders should engage\n\n\nABOUT YOU\n\n - 8–12+ years of experience in executive communications, corporate communications, or related roles, ideally in a high-growth or enterprise technology environment\n\n - Proven experience supporting C-suite and senior executives with high-stakes communications\n\n - Exceptional writing, editing, and storytelling skills with strong executive judgment\n\n - Strategic thinker who can zoom out to shape narrative and zoom in to execute flawlessly\n\n - Highly organized, calm under pressure, and comfortable managing competing priorities with senior stakeholders\n\n - Strong collaborator who can influence without authority and navigate complex organizations\n\n - Familiarity with enterprise technology, data, AI, financial communications, or people-related communications strongly preferred\n\n\nWHY JOIN SNOWFLAKE?\n\nAt Snowflake, you’ll help define how our most senior leaders communicate with employees, customers, investors, and the world. This role offers a rare opportunity to operate as a strategic partner to executive leadership while shaping the narrative of one of the most influential companies in modern data and AI.\n\nIf you’re energized by executive presence, big ideas, and high-impact storytelling, we’d love to hear from you.\n\nEvery Snowflake employee is expected to follow the company’s confidentiality and security standards for handling sensitive data. Snowflake employees must abide by the company’s data security plan as an essential part of their duties. It is every employee's duty to keep customer information secure and confidential.\n\nSnowflake is growing fast, and we’re scaling our team to help enable and accelerate our growth. We are looking for people who share our values, challenge ordinary thinking, and push the pace of innovation while building a future for themselves and Snowflake.\n\nHow do you want to make your impact?\n\nFor jobs located in the United States, please visit the job posting on the Snowflake Careers Site for salary and benefits information: careers.snowflake.com http://careers.snowflake.com",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
